==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entirety
<hw>En*tire"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Entireness</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OF.
<ets>entieret⟦eacute⟧</ets>. Cf. <er>Integrity</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of being entire; completeness; <as>as, <ex>entirely</ex>
of interest</as>.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is entire; the whole.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

